title: Appointments to the Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
The Government announced today (March 28) the re-appointment of two members and 
appointment of one new member to the Hospital Authority for a two-year term with 
effect from April 1. Mr David Lie-A-Cheong Tai-chong and Mr Gregory So Kam-leung have been 
re-appointed as members to the Hospital Authority. Ms Lau Ka-shi has been 
appointed as a new member. Ms Lau is the Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of Bank Consortium 
Trust Company Ltd. She is also a member of the Community Investment and

Trust Company Ltd. She is also a member of the Community Investment and 
Inclusion Fund Committee, Mandatory Provident Fund Industry Schemes Committee 
and Women's Commission. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, welcomed the new member to the 
board. He also thanked the outgoing member of the authority, Mrs Gloria Ng Wong 
Yee-man for her advice and contribution to the Hospital Authority. Mrs Ng will 
retire from the board on April 1 after having served on the board for six years. With effect from April 1, the authority will comprise a chairman, 20

non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the authority. The new membership list is as follows: Chairman:
